    • getForwardCaller

      @NotNull @NotNull TriFunction<Object,Class<?>,List<Class<?>>,Object> getForwardCaller()
      Retrieves the forward caller function used for type conversions.

      The BiFunction returned by this method is used to convert objects from one type to another during the deserialization process. It takes an Object as input and the target Class, then returns an instance of the target type.

      Returns:
      A BiFunction that performs type conversions, taking an Object and a target Class, and returning an instance of the target type.
